single, safe, copy-paste Bash script that will completely remove Docker, containerd, Kind, and Kubernetes leftovers on Ubuntu.

You can save this as cleanup-docker-kind.sh and run it once.
This is idempotent (won‚Äôt break if something is already gone).

üßπ FULL CLEANUP SCRIPT (Docker + Kind + K8s)
#!/bin/bash

set -e

echo "=============================="
echo " FULL DOCKER + KIND CLEANUP"
echo "=============================="

echo "[1/9] Stopping Docker & container services..."
sudo systemctl stop docker docker.socket containerd 2>/dev/null || true

echo "[2/9] Deleting all Kind clusters (if any)..."
if command -v kind >/dev/null 2>&1; then
  for c in $(kind get clusters 2>/dev/null); do
    kind delete cluster --name "$c" || true
  done
fi

echo "[3/9] Removing Docker containers related to kind..."
docker rm -f $(docker ps -aq --filter "name=kind") 2>/dev/null || true

echo "[4/9] Purging Docker & container packages..."
sudo apt-get purge -y \
  docker-ce \
  docker-ce-cli \
  docker-ce-rootless-extras \
  docker-buildx-plugin \
  docker-compose-plugin \
  docker.io \
  containerd \
  runc || true

echo "[5/9] Removing Docker data directories..."
sudo rm -rf /var/lib/docker
sudo rm -rf /var/lib/containerd

echo "[6/9] Removing user Docker config..."
rm -rf ~/.docker

echo "[7/9] Removing Docker group..."
sudo groupdel docker 2>/dev/null || true

echo "[8/9] Removing Docker APT repo & keys..."
sudo rm -f /etc/apt/sources.list.d/docker.list
sudo rm -f /etc/apt/keyrings/docker.gpg

echo "[9/9] Cleaning Kubernetes configs..."
rm -rf ~/.kube

echo "Updating apt cache..."
sudo apt-get update -y

echo "======================================"
echo " CLEANUP COMPLETE ‚úÖ"
echo " Docker, Kind, Kubernetes are removed"
echo "======================================"
echo ""
echo "Recommended: reboot the system"
echo "sudo reboot"

‚ñ∂Ô∏è How to use it
nano cleanup-docker-kind.sh
# paste the script


Make it executable:

chmod +x cleanup-docker-kind.sh


Run it:

./cleanup-docker-kind.sh


(Optional but strongly recommended)

sudo reboot

‚úÖ After reboot, verify (must all fail)
docker --version
kind get clusters
kubectl version


If they error out ‚Üí perfect üëå
